          "id": "tldr-ai:2023-03-22:o008",
          "order": 3,
          "title": "CLIP GOES 3D",
          "summary": "CG3D proposes a framework for zero-shot 3D geometric feature extraction by training a 3D encoder using point clouds, rendered 2D images, and text. Contrastive loss aligns features in a multimodal embedding space, and prompt tuning with trainable input parameters overcomes distribution shift issues. CG3D demonstrates impressive zero-shot, open-scene understanding, and retrieval capabilities, and serves as a strong starting weight for downstream 3D recognition tasks.",
          "url": "https://github.com/deeptibhegde/CLIP-goes-3D?utm_source=tldrai",
